<item>
<title>Making Google Maps more accessible</title>
<link>http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/456bereastreet/~3/471445038/</link>
<dc:creator>Roger Johansson</dc:creator>

<category>Accessibility</category>

<category>JavaScript</category>

<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.456bereastreet.com/archive/200812/making_google_maps_more_accessible/</guid>

<description>&lt;p class="preamble"&gt;It has become very popular to use the &lt;a href="http://code.google.com/apis/maps/"&gt;Google Maps API&lt;/a&gt; to add maps to websites. While the maps work fine for most users, unfortunately Google Maps does not by default work without JavaScript – when there is no JavaScript support, you don’t get a map.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fortunately it is quite easy (but not very common) to provide a fallback for users who do not have JavaScript enabled in their browser by using the &lt;a href="http://code.google.com/apis/maps/documentation/staticmaps/"&gt;Google Static Maps API&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Google Static Maps API lets you embed a map as a plain image in various formats. The developers guide explains the many options you have when it comes to configuring the static maps.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So next time you use the Google Maps API to put a map on a website, take a couple of minutes to add a static fallback for users without JavaScript.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While we’re on the topic of making Google Maps work for more people, I recommend reading Patrick H. Lauke’s article on creating &lt;a href="http://dev.opera.com/articles/view/keyboard-accessible-google-maps/"&gt;Keyboard-accessible Google Maps&lt;/a&gt;. Making Google Maps usable without a mouse requires a bit of hacking, but the end result is well worth it.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Posted in &lt;a href="http://www.456bereastreet.com/archive/categories/accessibility/" rel="tag"&gt;Accessibility&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="http://www.456bereastreet.com/archive/categories/javascript/" rel="tag"&gt;JavaScript&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
&lt;a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~f/456bereastreet?a=yEPIo"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~f/456bereastreet?i=yEPIo" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~f/456bereastreet?a=9Oozo"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~f/456bereastreet?i=9Oozo" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~f/456bereastreet?a=C0hnO"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~f/456bereastreet?i=C0hnO" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~f/456bereastreet?a=YyLso"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~f/456bereastreet?i=YyLso" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
